.Dd 2015-10-08
.Dt MKDIR 1
.Os sbase
.Sh NAME
.Nm mkdir
.Nd create directories
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl p
.Op Fl m Ar mode
.Ar name ...
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
creates a directory for each
.Ar name
if it does not already exist.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width Ds
.It Fl m
Set the file
.Ar mode
of newly created directories.
See
.Xr chmod 1 .
.It Fl p
Also create necessary parent directories and
do not fail if
.Ar name
already exists.
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr mkdir 2
.Sh STANDARDS
The
.Nm
utility is compliant with the
.St -p1003.1-2013
specification.
